    subgraph "Common Mistakes"
        L1["❌ Over-committing
        Buy RIs without usage analysis
        Impact: Pay for unused capacity"]

        L2["❌ Wrong instance type
        Standard RI for changing workload
        Solution: Use Compute SP or Convertible RI"]

        L3["❌ Ignoring expiration
        RIs expire, revert to On-Demand
        Solution: 30-day expiration alerts"]

        L4["❌ No Spot strategy
        All On-Demand for interruptible work
        Solution: 70-80% Spot for batch jobs"]

        L5["❌ No monitoring
        Low utilization goes unnoticed
        Solution: Weekly RI/SP utilization review"]
    end

    subgraph "Implementation Workflow"
        M1["1. Analyze Usage (30 days)
        Cost Explorer → Rightsizing Recommendations"]

        M2["2. Identify Steady-State
        Baseline: 24/7 workloads
        Variable: Bursty workloads"]

        M3["3. Calculate Commitment
        RI/SP for 70-80% of baseline
        Keep 20-30% On-Demand buffer"]

        M4["4. Choose RI/SP Type
        Maximum flexibility: Compute SP
        Committed family: EC2 Instance SP
        Maximum discount: Standard RI"]

        M5["5. Purchase and Monitor
        Buy incrementally (start with 50%)
        Monitor utilization weekly
        Adjust quarterly"]

        M1 --> M2 --> M3 --> M4 --> M5
    end

